arStrings.szText: "How did you come to be friends with Akarat?"
He helped me bear the weight of the stone. I...I buckled under that weight, on the river into Nahantu. It was bad. I was losing myself.
He had called me to Nahantu, but I didnâ€™t truly see him until after the boat. I thought I was seeing mad visions, at first. But he was real, and he soothed me, and brought me back to myself.
I would already be lost to Mephisto without him.
